        <Parent_String>percussion idiophones: solid-bodied [300209184], percussion idiophones [300195371], directly struck idiophones [300041659], struck idiophones [300041657], idiophones [300041646], sound devices by acoustical characteristics [300041621], sound devices (equipment) [300387677], Sound Devices (hierarchy name) [300041619], Furnishings and Equipment (hierarchy name) [300264551], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Percussion instruments found worldwide in a variety of forms, consisting basically of a set of two or more tuned bars of wood, bamboo, or synthetic material, supported at two nodes of vibration and struck with sticks or hammers; resonators are often included, either for each individual key or for all keys as a set.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Instrumentos de percusión que se encuentran en todo el mundo en una variedad de formas, consistentes básicamente en un conjunto de dos o más barras afinadas de madera, bambú o material sintético, sujetas a dos nódulos de vibración, y que se golpean con palillos o macillos; a menudo incluyen resonadores ya sea para cada barra individual o para todas las barras en conjunto.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Slaginstrumenten, in allerlei vormen bestaande uit 2 of meer gestemde toetsen van hout, bamboe of synthetisch materiaal, steunend op 2 vibratiepunten, met klankbodems onder iedere toets afzonderlijk of onder alle toetsen gezamenlijk; bespeeld met stokjes of hamertjes; wereldwijd.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052452/Encyclopedie van muziekinstrumenten (1977)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指分佈世界各地的打擊樂器，形式各異，基本為一組兩根以上調音過的木條、竹條、或是合成材料條狀物所組成，在兩個振動節點架以支柱，以棒子或槌子敲擊，不管是單鍵或是成組的鍵經常都包含有共鳴器。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Instrumentos de percussão encontrados em todo o mundo nas mais variadas formas, constituídos basicamente por um conjunto de duas ou mais barras afinadas de madeira, bambu ou material sintético, apoiadas em dois nós de vibração e percutidas com paus ou martelos; ressonadores são frequentemente incluídos, seja para cada tecla individual ou para todas as teclas como um conjunto.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000316/CVAA-BR</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109633/CVAA-BR Consortium (2020-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Schlaginstrument, das weltweit in einer Vielfalt von Formen vorkommt. Es besteht hauptsächlich aus einem Satz von zwei oder mehr gestimmten Platten oder Stäben aus Holz, Bambus oder synthetischem Material, die an den zwei Hauptschwingungsknoten auf Isolatoren lagern und mit Schlägern oder Hämmern angeschlagen werden; oft sind Resonatoren angefügt, entweder für jeden einzelnen Ton oder für alle Töne in einer Reihe.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
